Package controller

Interface Features

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NewController
    public interface Features
    This interface represents the operations on controller. It is the central part of the program and is called by the main method.

    • Method Detail

      • createPortfolio

        void createPortfolio​(java.lang.String portfolioName)
        This method is used to create a portfolio with a given portfolio name. A portfolios should have unique names for a particular user.
        Parameters:
        portfolioName - String which is unique for each user

      • buyStocks

        void buyStocks​(java.lang.String symbol,
               int numberOfShares,
               java.lang.String date,
               float commissionFee,
               boolean creating)
        This method is used to buy a stock and add it to this user's active portfolio. A flexible portfolio contains a hashmap which stores all these stocks. To add a stock to the portfolio user needs to enter Stock Symbol, number of shares he wants, date on which he wants and the transaction cost associated with it.
        Parameters:
        symbol - String which should be a valid.
        numberOfShares - float which is the number of shares the user wants of that company.
        date - LocalDate date on which he wants to purchase.
        commissionFee - float which is transaction associated for this transaction.
        creating - boolean to check if it is called while creating.

      • sellStocks

        void sellStocks​(java.lang.String symbol,
                float numberOfShares,
                java.lang.String date,
                float commissionFee)
        This method is used to sell a stock from user's active portfolio. It checks if it is possible to sell the stocks and sells them only if it is possible. To sell a stock from a portfolio user needs to enter Stock Symbol, number of shares he wants, date on which he wants to sell and the transaction cost associated with it.
        Parameters:
        symbol - String which should be a valid.
        numberOfShares - float which is the number of shares the user wants to sell.
        date - LocalDate date on which he wants to sell.
        commissionFee - float which is transaction associated for this transaction.

      • getCostBasis

        float getCostBasis​(java.lang.String date)
        This method is used to get the cost basis of this user's active portfolio.Cost Basis shows the total amount of money invested in a portfolio by a specific date.
        Parameters:
        date - String which is given by the user
        Returns:
        float which has the total amount of money invested in a portfolio by a specific date

      • getTotalValue

        float getTotalValue​(java.lang.String date)
        This method is used to get the total value of this user's active portfolio on a certain date. If weekend values are govern then it tells the user to enter a date which is not weekend.
        Parameters:
        date - String which is given by the user
        Returns:
        total value of the portfolio on a certain date.

      • save

        void save()
        This method is used to save this user in a file. Save option is given to the user in the menu. It stores all the data into local file system.

      • loadPortfolio

        void loadPortfolio​(java.lang.String portfolioName)
        This method is used to load a portfolio with a given portfolio name. This is called by the user to make a portfolio active and do operations like getComposition and getTotal value on a certain date.
        Parameters:
        portfolioName - String which is unique for a user.

      • investOnDate

        void investOnDate​(java.lang.String date,
                  float amount,
                  float commissionFee,
                  java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Float> stocks,
                  boolean creating)
        This method is used to invest a specific amount in an existing flexible portfolio on a specific date by specifying the weights of how that money should be invested in each stock inside that portfolio.
        Parameters:
        date - LocalDate date on which he wants to purchase.
        amount - float amount which the user wants to invest.
        commissionFee - float which is cost associated for this transaction.
        stocks - Hashmap of stocks which contains the Symbol as key and weight as value.
        creating - boolean to check if it is called while creating.

      • dollarCost

        void dollarCost​(java.lang.String startDate,
                java.lang.String endDate,
                int interval,
                float amount,
                float commissionFee,
                java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Float> stocks,
                boolean creating)
        This method is used to create a portfolio using dollar-cost averaging as specified above, and query cost basis and value of such a portfolio at a specific date.
        Parameters:
        startDate - LocalDate date on which he wants to start the purchase.
        endDate - LocalDate date on which he wants to end the purchase.
        interval - float interval in which the user wants to invest.
        amount - float amount which the user wants to invest.
        commissionFee - float which is cost associated for this transaction.
        stocks - Hashmap of stocks which contains the Symbol as key and weight as value.
        creating - boolean to check if it is called while creating.

      • createUser

        void createUser​(java.lang.String userName,
                float balance)
        This method creates a user from a username and initial balance. This method is called which creating a user from the program.
        Parameters:
        userName - String username which is unique for a user
        balance - float balance which is entered by the user

      • loadUser

        void loadUser​(java.lang.String userName)
        This method loads a user from a file with the username as the file name. It loads all the data from that file into the program.
        Parameters:
        userName - String username which is unique for a user

      • getActivePortfolio

        java.lang.String getActivePortfolio()
        This method is used to get the current active portfolio which is loaded.
        Returns:
        return string which is name of the current active portfolio.

      • getListOfPortfolios

        java.lang.String getListOfPortfolios()
        This method is used to get the list of portfolios of the current user.
        Returns:
        return string which has the list of portfolios.

      • getPlot

        PlotPair getPlot​(java.lang.String startDate,
                 java.lang.String endDate,
                 int maximumPlots)
        This method is used to generate plotting values such as dates and values which are used for plotting.
        Parameters:
        startDate - LocalDate start date of the range.
        endDate - LocalDate end date of the range.
        maximumPlots - int which is the maximum number of points on x-axis of the plot.
        Returns:
        return a PlotPair which is a custom datatype created by us to return dates and values
